Cucmber Noodle Pad Thai 
  --Jodi Moreno

Peanut Sauce:
¼ c peanut or almond butter
2 tbsp tamari or coconut aminos
2 tbsp brown rice vinegar
1 tbsp freshly squeezed lime juice
Dash or 2 of hot sauce
¼" piece ginger
1 small garlic clove, minced
2 tsp honey
1 tsp toasted sesame oil
2 tbsp water

Put the peanut butter, tamari, vinegar, lime juice, hot sauce, ginger, garlic, honey and sesame oil in a food processor and run continuously until smooth. Add ~2 tbsp of water, or just enough that the mixture will coat the back of a spoon. Store in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.

Cucmber Salad
2 cucumbers, julienned or spiralized lengthwise
1 medium green zucchini, julienned or spiralized lengthwise
1 medium yellow zucchini, julienned or spiralized lengthwise
¼ c peanut sauce
3 scallions, white and light-green parts only, thinly sliced
¼ c peanuts or cashews, finely chopped
Handful of cilantro, roughly chopped
7 to 10 basil leaves, roughly chopped
Nori gomasio, for serving (optional)
Toasted sesame or hemp seeds, for serving (optional)

In a large bowl, toss together the cucumber and zucchini noodles. Spoon in the peanut sauce little by little until the noodles are dressed as much as you like. Toss to combine, then sprinkle with the scallions, nuts, cilantro, basil and optional ingredients to serve.
